The paper deals with the study of auction formats and their efficiency, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and computational economics (cs.EC). The use of upper and lower bounds on the Price of Anarchy involves algorithmic techniques and optimization, which could be classified under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the evaluation of auction formats and their applications could also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
